race.description: All Aspects Roofing F&M Mdn Plate
race.comment: ALABAMA CHARM (4) travelled a bit closer than normal and failed to finish off last time out over this distance at Kembla. Usually reliable so at only the third run of the campaign she can turn things around. FLAXLANDS (8) turned in a real eye-catcher recently over 1300m at Warwick Farm, charging home from last in a small field to be beaten just half a length. A lack of pace will work against but this lightly raced filly cannot be ruled out. ALL KIRKED UP (5) did a good job on debut at Canberra and will be more effective over an extra 200m. APADANA (6) has run home well in both career starts suggesting the step up to 1400m here will be right up her gate. Each-way.
